<subSubSection id="F427809F36E3507F2FCADF31CC5F33B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="62D16B3506E4AB6B58A786F187D6EAC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="429721B3548219977CFA9EAD8BE4C8C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="114DDD01D8ECDD40B1E87A9E231FF30A" baseAuthorityName="Mao" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster dignus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dignus">
<emphasis id="8CF70592DA6A51151EF8CE75C531F0D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster dignus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other members of 
<taxonomicName id="943CFE81302FE61BFE4924A5683063DF" authorityName="Dangerfield, Austin &amp; Whitfield" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="06ACD49E5E8383EC97455675749E8E3E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having longer body length (~ 7.5mm); fore wing apically infuscate with pale stigma (Key Image 5A); basal spur on hind tibia 0.67 
<normalizedToken id="13F698DD1A8BF994232F14B35827EB70" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than length of basitarsus; T1 pale; T2 mostly pale, medially and submedially dark (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0A346A2C4E77D3F8AF903386B61383A1" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Dorsal habitus of Retusigaster dignus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668118" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="13B90CBF2F8BCC5C9CE17B01CE51FBC1" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668118" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="4550AD01BD752679DEA32F1909DCC521" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="5FD18D0E0674C840DDB9E0E634650439" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Figure 1.</emphasis>
Dorsal habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="9B056939FA2BCAFF1FD3054113FFF1E7" baseAuthorityName="Mao" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster dignus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dignus">
<emphasis id="7B347DA899EF7D87DE988E808482CB9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster dignus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
